WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.500
<v Dr. Smith>Welcome to Introduction to Computer Science, lecture five.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:09.200
<v Dr. Smith>Today we'll explore data structures and their applications.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:14.800
<v Student>Dr. Smith, could you explain the difference between arrays and linked lists?

00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:20.000
<v Dr. Smith>Excellent question! Arrays store elements in contiguous memory locations.

00:00:20.500 --> 00:00:25.300
<v Dr. Smith>Linked lists, on the other hand, use pointers to connect elements dynamically.
